d circumstances. The experiment that we demonstrated will show how effective it is to apply this model to deal with the price conflict in the oil industry, thereby yielding the most optimal balance between the stakeholders, which could be a promising solution.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:file {\"id\":294,\"href\":\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Group1_Thursday_A-game-theoretical-approach-to-solve-the-oil-price-problem-using-the-NSGA-II-model.pdf\",\"displayPreview\":true} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-file\"><object class=\"wp-block-file__embed\" data=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Group1_Thursday_A-game-theoretical-approach-to-solve-the-oil-price-problem-using-the-NSGA-II-model.pdf\" type=\"application/pdf\" style=\"width:100%;height:600px\" aria-label=\"Group1_Thursday_A game-theoretical approach to solve the oil price problem using the NSGA-II model\"></object><a id=\"wp-block-file--media-1875fb61-d6a8-45ed-9f1e-7f1056dbc3b0\" href=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Group1_Thursday_A-game-theoretical-approach-to-solve-the-oil-price-problem-using-the-NSGA-II-model.pdf\">Group1_Thursday_A game-theoretical approach to solve the oil price problem using the NSGA-II model</a><a href=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Group1_Thursday_A-game-theoretical-approach-to-solve-the-oil-price-problem-using-the-NSGA-II-model.pdf\" class=\"wp-block-file__button wp-element-button\" download aria-describedby=\"wp-block-file--media-1875fb61-d6a8-45ed-9f1e-7f1056dbc3b0\">Download</a></div>\n<!-- /wp:file -->','A game-theoretical approach to solve the oilprice problem using the NSGA-II model','','inherit','closed','closed','','312-revision-v1','','','2024-03-05 11:44:33','2024-03-05 11:44:33','',312,'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=313',0,'revision','',0),(314,1,'2024-03-05 11:45:27','2024-03-05 11:45:27','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><br>Year: Spring 2022</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><br><strong>Instructor: Dr. Trinh Bao Ngoc</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><br>Students: </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Nguyen Thi Thanh Huyen</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Nguyen Duy Anh</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Vu Thi Bich Phuong</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Can Thi Mai Anh</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Nguyen Thi Diem Quynh</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontSize\":\"medium\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\"><strong>Abstract</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Cooperation between countries and different economies is an inevitable trend for development in all aspects, but contradictions and trading conflicts still exist even though they have been resolved by many methods. This article suggests the use of game theory to resolve conflicts of economic cooperation between countries in the WTO participating in global cooperation. Therefore, the purpose of using game theory is to understand and analyze the behaviour or decisions of global cooperative countries that are one the typical cases of conflict situations. Based on the FEMO [1] algorithm model, it will show the main tensions when cooperating based on trade and protectionist principles, and point out common causes leading to domestic conflicts and conflicts when cooperating between countries families. From there, we came up with issues that need to be resolved including unfair competition between economic cooperation partners, the need to use domestic goods and taxes caused by the trade war to minimize failures, aim to solve problems and offer some strategic choices for players who use game theory joining the world trade market.<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:file {\"id\":296,\"href\":\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/SS207_Monday.pdf\",\"displayPreview\":true} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-file\"><object class=\"wp-block-file__embed\" data=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/SS207_Monday.pdf\" type=\"application/pdf\" style=\"width:100%;height:600px\" aria-label=\"SS207_Monday\"></object><a id=\"wp-block-file--media-dd403067-6ac5-40e5-aef8-cd1bccae366a\" href=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/SS207_Monday.pdf\">SS207_Monday</a><a href=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/SS207_Monday.pdf\" class=\"wp-block-file__button wp-element-button\" download aria-describedby=\"wp-block-file--media-dd403067-6ac5-40e5-aef8-cd1bccae366a\">Download</a></div>\n<!-- /wp:file -->','Application of Game Theory in trading conflictresolution of global cooperation in economicsbetween member countries in WTO using FairEvolutionary Multiobjective Optimizer (FEMO)','','inherit','closed','closed','','306-revision-v1','','','2024-03-05 11:45:27','2024-03-05 11:45:27','',306,'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=314',0,'revision','',0),(315,1,'2024-03-05 11:49:07','2024-03-05 11:49:07','','books-4095266_640','','inherit','open','closed','','books-4095266_640','','','2024-03-05 11:49:07','2024-03-05 11:49:07','',0,'http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/books-4095266_640.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(316,1,'2024-03-05 11:51:15','2024-03-05 11:51:15','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Hanyu Gu, Hue Chi Lam , Yakov Zinder<br>School of Mathematical and Physical Sciences, University of Technology Sydney,<br>PO Box 123, Broadway, NSW 2007, Australia</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontSize\":\"medium\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\"><strong>Abstract</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left\">This study addresses the scheduling problem where every job requires several types of resources. At every point in time, the capacity of resources is limited. When necessary, the capacity can be increased at a cost. Each job has a due date, and the processing times of jobs are random variables with a known probability distribution. The considered problem is to determine a schedule that minimises the total cost, which consists of the cost incurred due to the violation of resource limits and the total tardiness of jobs. A genetic algorithm enhanced by local search is proposed. The sample average approximation method is used to construct a confidence interval for the optimality gap of the obtained solutions. Computational study on the application of the sample average approximation method and genetic algorithm is presented. It is revealed that the proposed method is capable of providing high-quality solutions to large instances in a reasonable time.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:file {\"id\":277,\"href\":\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/A-hybrid-genetic-algorithm-for-scheduling-jobs-s_2022_EURO-Journal-on-Comput.pdf\",\"displayPreview\":true} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-file\"><object class=\"wp-block-file__embed\" data=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/A-hybrid-genetic-algorithm-for-scheduling-jobs-s_2022_EURO-Journal-on-Comput.pdf\" type=\"application/pdf\" style=\"width:100%;height:600px\" aria-label=\"A-hybrid-genetic-algorithm-for-scheduling-jobs-s_2022_EURO-Journal-on-Comput\"></object><a id=\"wp-block-file--media-27f9beac-ebee-4fe7-be08-41360a06613c\" href=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/A-hybrid-genetic-algorithm-for-scheduling-jobs-s_2022_EURO-Journal-on-Comput.pdf\">A-hybrid-genetic-algorithm-for-scheduling-jobs-s_2022_EURO-Journal-on-Comput</a><a href=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/A-hybrid-genetic-algorithm-for-scheduling-jobs-s_2022_EURO-Journal-on-Comput.pdf\" class=\"wp-block-file__button wp-element-button\" download aria-describedby=\"wp-block-file--media-27f9beac-ebee-4fe7-be08-41360a06613c\">Download</a></div>\n<!-- /wp:file -->','A hybrid genetic algorithm for scheduling jobssharing multiple resources under uncertainty','','inherit','closed','closed','','286-autosave-v1','','','2024-03-05 11:51:15','2024-03-05 11:51:15','',286,'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=316',0,'revision','',0),(317,1,'2024-03-05 11:51:32','2024-03-05 11:51:32','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Hanyu Gu, Hue Chi Lam , Yakov Zinder<br>School of Mathematical and Physical Sciences, University of Technology Sydney,<br>PO Box 123, Broadway, NSW 2007, Australia</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontSize\":\"medium\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\"><strong>Abstract</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left\">This study addresses the scheduling problem where every job requires several types of resources. At every point in time, the capacity of resources is limited. When necessary, the capacity can be increased at a cost. Each job has a due date, and the processing times of jobs are random variables with a known probability distribution. The considered problem is to determine a schedule that minimises the total cost, which consists of the cost incurred due to the violation of resource limits and the total tardiness of jobs. A genetic algorithm enhanced by local search is proposed. The sample average approximation method is used to construct a confidence interval for the optimality gap of the obtained solutions. Computational study on the application of the sample average approximation method and genetic algorithm is presented. It is revealed that the proposed method is capable of providing high-quality solutions to large instances in a reasonable time.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:file {\"id\":277,\"href\":\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/A-hybrid-genetic-algorithm-for-scheduling-jobs-s_2022_EURO-Journal-on-Comput.pdf\",\"displayPreview\":tr